==Korean==

===Verb===
'''있다''' (''issda, itta'')
#To be (in a place)
#*뉴욕은 미국에 '''있다'''. (''nyuyok-eun migug-e '''issda'''.'') New York '''is''' in the United States. 
#*물속에 물고기가 '''있다'''. (''mulsog-e mulgogi-ga '''issda'''.'') There '''are''' fish in the water. 
#To have
#*그녀는 남자 친구가 '''있다'''. (''geunyeo-neun namja chingu-ga '''issda'''.'') She '''has''' a boyfriend. 
#(''auxiliary: progressive or otherwise'')
#*서 '''있다''' (''seo '''issda''''') To '''be''' standing
#*울고 '''있다''' (''ulgo '''issda''''') To '''be''' crying
#*모여 '''있다''' (''moyeo '''issda''''') To '''be''' gathered 

====Antonyms====
*[[없다]] (''eobs-da, eopta'') To lack, to be absent  

